description: The investment seeks to track the investment results of the S&P International Preferred Stock IndexTM composed of preferred stocks of non-U.S. developed markets. The fund will invest at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of the index and in investments that are substantially identical to the component securities of the index and may invest up to 20% of its assets in certain futures, options and swap contracts, cash and cash equivalents, as well as in securities not included in the index, but which BFA believes will help the fund track the index. The fund is non-diversified.
name: iShares International Preferred Stock ETF
